            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Yes I see what you mean. I'm not sure to understand all the documentation of `command-attributes`, but I think there is also `range`, `count`  and `addr` (resp. doc sections are: `command-range`, `command-count` and `command-addr`), which are more than boolean flags.\r\n\r\nTo me the phrasing `\"Set boolean |command-attributes| such as [...]\"` is misleading since the above mentioned arguments are not boolean, and one needs a bit more info to know which value they should take. Also I think it's nice to know which arguments exist from the `nvim_create_user_command()` doc section, and that there are more info on them in the `map` doc.\r\n\r\nI would suggest at least listing that these arguments exist, and link to each of their  doc section in `map`.\r\n\r\nSomething like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n- `range` see |:command-range|\r\n- `count` see |:command-count|\r\n- `addr` see |:command-addr|\r\n```\r\n\r\nIdeally with a one-liner descripton of the nature of the argument (unfortunately I don't really understand the in-depth on these).\r\n\r\nIf you agree, I can edit the PR in this spirit",
            "commit_id": "a35658b5782e18fc4b9bbe17422c35a1d6830efd",
